<subSubSection id="C3086534FF87D236FCE8C84ED1ACF954" pageId="7" pageNumber="183" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAD36BFFF87D236FCE8C84ED0D9FBD4" blockId="7.[835,1475,1037,1125]" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FCE8C84ED6A2FB94" bold="true" box="[835,952,1037,1061]" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognised by the following set of characters: antennal segment II dark brown (
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FB0EC86ED1FCFBF4" box="[1189,1254,1069,1093]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[136,180,2035,2057]" captionTargetBox="[194,1415,189,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-58@1.[194,1415,189,2020]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Dorsal habitus photographs: 1, 2, Dashymenia artchawakomi (1. holotype, 2, paratype, male); 3, 4, D. capillosa (3. Female, Thai: Nk. Ratchasima: Sakaerat Environ. R.S., upper tower, coll. T. Yasunaga, 29 October 2008, 4. Female, Ryukyus: Ishigaki: Mt. Nosokodake, coll. T. Nakata, 14 August 2002); 5, 6, D. gorczycai (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502024/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); scutellum blackish (
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FCE0C80ED692FBD4" box="[843,904,1101,1125]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[136,180,2035,2057]" captionTargetBox="[194,1415,189,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-58@1.[194,1415,189,2020]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Dorsal habitus photographs: 1, 2, Dashymenia artchawakomi (1. holotype, 2, paratype, male); 3, 4, D. capillosa (3. Female, Thai: Nk. Ratchasima: Sakaerat Environ. R.S., upper tower, coll. T. Yasunaga, 29 October 2008, 4. Female, Ryukyus: Ishigaki: Mt. Nosokodake, coll. T. Nakata, 14 August 2002); 5, 6, D. gorczycai (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502024/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); endosoma as described below and depicted in 
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FAD8C80ED0A5FBD4" box="[1395,1471,1101,1125]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[162,1452,190,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[161,1458,181,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–19. Male genitalia. 7–9, Bothriomiris ernsti; 10, B. lugubris; 11–13, Dashymenia artchawakomi; 14–16, D. capillosa; 17–19, D. gorczycai. 7, 10, 11, 14, 17, Endosoma (dorsal view); 8, 12, 15, 18, Left paramere (right lateral view); 9, 13, 16, 19, Right paramere (dorsal view). AES = anterior endosomal sclerite; APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; MES = medial endosoma sclerite; PES = posterior endosomal sclerite; PB = paramere body." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502030/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36BFFF87D236FCE8C8CDD1B5FB54" blockId="7.[835,1474,1165,1253]" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D3CFF87D236FC56C8CDD18DFB14" authorityName="Wolski &amp; Yasunaga" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Yasunaga &amp; Miyamoto" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1021,1175,1165,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Bothriomiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yakushima">
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FC56C8CDD18DFB14" box="[1021,1175,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">D. yakushima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing a similar body coloration but this species has the shorter labium and differently shaped male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36BFFF87D236FCE8C94ED1ACF954" blockId="7.[835,1475,1293,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FCE8C94ED6FBFA94" bold="true" box="[835,993,1293,1317]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FC46C94ED174FA94" box="[1005,1134,1293,1317]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[162,1452,190,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[161,1458,181,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–19. Male genitalia. 7–9, Bothriomiris ernsti; 10, B. lugubris; 11–13, Dashymenia artchawakomi; 14–16, D. capillosa; 17–19, D. gorczycai. 7, 10, 11, 14, 17, Endosoma (dorsal view); 8, 12, 15, 18, Left paramere (right lateral view); 9, 13, 16, 19, Right paramere (dorsal view). AES = anterior endosomal sclerite; APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; MES = medial endosoma sclerite; PES = posterior endosomal sclerite; PB = paramere body." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502030/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Figs. 14–16</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FBD4C94ED1FCFA94" box="[1151,1254,1293,1317]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FB58C94ED05AFA94" box="[1267,1344,1293,1317]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[162,1452,190,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[161,1458,181,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–19. Male genitalia. 7–9, Bothriomiris ernsti; 10, B. lugubris; 11–13, Dashymenia artchawakomi; 14–16, D. capillosa; 17–19, D. gorczycai. 7, 10, 11, 14, 17, Endosoma (dorsal view); 8, 12, 15, 18, Left paramere (right lateral view); 9, 13, 16, 19, Right paramere (dorsal view). AES = anterior endosomal sclerite; APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; MES = medial endosoma sclerite; PES = posterior endosomal sclerite; PB = paramere body." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502030/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Endosoma with AES long, mostly cylindrical, thin and arched slightly broadened and pointed apically; AES situated at apical half of endosoma, relatively broad, cylindrical on apical half, gradually becoming narrower toward apex; MES weakly curved along entire length, situated on basal half of endosoma, nearly ellipsoidal on basal two thirds, thin and cylindrical on apical one third; PES occupying most of basal part of endosoma, basal half nearly triangular, apical half bifurcate, with two sharply pointed branches. 
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FB6BCA6ED042F9F4" box="[1216,1368,1581,1605]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Left paramere</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FACDCA6ED0AFF9F4" box="[1382,1461,1581,1605]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[162,1452,190,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[161,1458,181,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–19. Male genitalia. 7–9, Bothriomiris ernsti; 10, B. lugubris; 11–13, Dashymenia artchawakomi; 14–16, D. capillosa; 17–19, D. gorczycai. 7, 10, 11, 14, 17, Endosoma (dorsal view); 8, 12, 15, 18, Left paramere (right lateral view); 9, 13, 16, 19, Right paramere (dorsal view). AES = anterior endosomal sclerite; APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; MES = medial endosoma sclerite; PES = posterior endosomal sclerite; PB = paramere body." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502030/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Apical process weakly curved with a dorsal margin arcuate and ventral margin sinuate; paramere body relatively broad; sensory lobe weakly convex. 
<emphasis id="B966EAADFF87D236FB31CACED056F914" box="[1178,1356,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Right paramere</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13292A3AFF87D236FAF4CACED0AEF914" box="[1375,1460,1677,1701]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[162,1452,190,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[161,1458,181,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–19. Male genitalia. 7–9, Bothriomiris ernsti; 10, B. lugubris; 11–13, Dashymenia artchawakomi; 14–16, D. capillosa; 17–19, D. gorczycai. 7, 10, 11, 14, 17, Endosoma (dorsal view); 8, 12, 15, 18, Left paramere (right lateral view); 9, 13, 16, 19, Right paramere (dorsal view). AES = anterior endosomal sclerite; APR = apical process; BPR = basal process; DSS = sclerotized portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma; MES = medial endosoma sclerite; PES = posterior endosomal sclerite; PB = paramere body." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502030/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="183">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Slender; apical process shortened, sharply pointed; paramere body with lateral margins sinuate.
